import numpy as np
from scipy.stats import lognorm, norm, truncnorm

# Define the target materials
target_materials = ['aluminium', 'gold', 'polypropylene', 'plastic']

# Function to generate a single sample
def generate_sample():
    # Target material (randomly chosen)
    target_material = np.random.choice(target_materials)

    # Target thickness (lognormal distribution)
    target_thickness = lognorm.rvs(0.593, scale=1.02, size=1)[0]

    # Pulse width (lognormal distribution with a minimum value of 24)
    pulse_width = truncnorm.rvs((30-24)/291, (12900-24)/291, loc=24, scale=291, size=1)[0]

    # Energy (lognormal distribution)
    energy = lognorm.rvs(2.35, scale=13.9, size=1)[0]

    # Spot size (normal distribution with a minimum value of 2.13 and a maximum value of 60)
    spot_size = truncnorm.rvs((3.3-2.13)/3.61, (60-2.13)/3.61, loc=2.13, scale=3.61, size=1)[0]

    # Intensity (lognormal distribution)
    intensity = lognorm.rvs(20.5, scale=np.log(5.10e20), size=1)[0]

    # Power (lognormal distribution)
    power = lognorm.rvs(13.7, scale=np.log(6.23e13), size=1)[0]

    # Cutoff energy (normal distribution)
    cutoff_energy = norm.rvs(loc=8.64, scale=np.sqrt(156), size=1)[0]

    return [target_material, target_thickness, pulse_width, energy, spot_size, intensity, power, cutoff_energy]

# Generate 25 samples
synthetic_data = [generate_sample() for _ in range(25)]

print(synthetic_data)
```
